`, `LastSentAt`\n- State transitions capture state changes from evaluation results\n- State persister saves states asynchronously; historian records state transitions\n\n## Notification Routing\n\n**Alert Router** (pkg/services/ngalert/sender/router.go:34-54):\n- `AlertsRouter.Send()` (line 316) routes alerts based on organization configuration\n- Routes to internal Alertmanager via `MultiOrgAlertmanager.AlertmanagerFor(orgID)`\n- Routes to external Alertmanager(s) if configured and enabled\n- Configuration determines if alerts go to internal only, external only, or both\n\n## Notification Dispatch\n\n**Internal Alertmanager** (pkg/services/ngalert/notifier/multiorg_alertmanager.go:92-118):\n- `MultiOrgAlertmanager` maintains per-organization `Alertmanager` instances\n- `PutAlerts()` adds alerts to the alertmanager's internal routing engine\n- Handles alert grouping, routing rules, silences, and notification suppression\n- Built on `github.com/grafana/alerting` library (GrafanaAlertmanager)\n\n**External Alertmanager** (pkg/services/ngalert/sender/sender.go:119-229):\n- `ExternalAlertmanager.SendAlerts()` (line 209) sends alerts to configured external Alertmanager(s)\n- Converts PostableAlerts to notifier Alert format\n- Uses service discovery to resolve Alertmanager targets\n- Implements queue management and batch sending via `Manager.Send()`\n- Sanitizes label names for Prometheus Alertmanager compatibility\n\n**Alert Notification** (pkg/services/ngalert/notifier/alertmanager.go:90-150):\n- `NewAlertmanager()` creates org-specific alertmanager instances\n- Uses `GrafanaAlertmanager` from grafana/alerting library\n- Implements maintenance operations for silences and notification logs\n- Handles notification group routing and receiver delivery\n\n## State Persistence\n\nState is persisted via `StatePersister` (pkg/services/ngalert/state/manager.go:35-37):\n- Async persister batches state saves\n- Sync persister saves per-rule state immediately after evaluation\n- State historian records audit trail of state transitions\n\nThe complete execution chain: Scheduler → Rule Evaluation → Condition Evaluation → State Transitions → Notification Router → Internal/External Notifiers → Receiver Handlers"
